  - context: object | string
  - options: { base?, documentLoader?, processingMode?, compactToRelative?: boolean }
- frame(input, frame, options): Promise<any>
  - options: { base?, documentLoader?, processingMode?, embed?: boolean, explicit?: boolean, omitGraph?: boolean }
- flatten(input, contextOrOptions): Promise<any>
- toRDF(input, options): Promise<string|object>
  - options: { format?: 'application/n-quads'|'internal', produceGeneralizedRdf?: boolean, documentLoader? }
  - returns: if format is 'application/n-quads' returns Promise<string> containing N-Quads; if 'internal' returns dataset object mapping graph names to arrays of quads.
- fromRDF(dataset, options): Promise<any>
  - dataset: string (N-Quads) or internal dataset object
  - options: { format?: 'application/n-quads'|'internal', useRdfType?: boolean, rdfDirection?: boolean }
- normalize(input, options): Promise<string>
  - options: { algorithm?: 'URDNA2015'|'URGNA2012', format?: 'application/n-quads' }

Document loader contract
- documentLoader(url) must return a Promise resolving to object: { contextUrl?: string, documentUrl: string, document: any }
- document returned for context requests must be either a JSON-LD context object or a JSON document containing @context to be processed.
- Custom loaders must handle caching, HTTP caching headers, content-type negotiation, and provide error details on fetch failures.

Configuration options that affect behaviour
- processingMode: 'json-ld-1.1' enables JSON-LD 1.1 behaviors (default); set to 'json-ld-1.0' for legacy rules.
- compactToRelative: when true, allows compacting IRIs to relative forms using @base and @vocab rules.
- produceGeneralizedRdf: when true, allows producing RDF datasets containing triples with blank nodes or non-standard constructs; false for strict RDF 1.1 compliance.

BEST PRACTICES AND PATTERNS
- Embed JSON-LD in HTML using a single script type="application/ld+json" per entity when possible; keep contexts small and import shared contexts via stable HTTPS IRI.
- Use remote shared contexts for consistent term mappings across services; host contexts with correct CORS and cache headers, and include link rel="alternate" when appropriate.
- Prefer compacted documents with a curated @context for public API responses to reduce payload and improve readability.
- For signing and canonicalization, convert to RDF dataset and run normalize with URDNA2015 to produce deterministic N-Quads.
- When publishing schema.org data, include canonical enumerations using schema.org IRIs via link or JSON-LD values to avoid parsing ambiguity.

TROUBLESHOOTING
- Invalid context errors: verify that @context entries are valid JSON objects or reachable IRIs; ensure document loader can fetch referenced contexts.
- Unexpected expansion/compaction shapes: check term definition @container and @type settings; use expand to see fully resolved IRIs and value objects.
- Blank node collisions: run normalize to assign deterministic canonical blank node identifiers before diffing or signing.
- RDF round-trip differences: ensure toRDF/fromRDF options match expected formats and useRdfType handling; prefer using JSON-LD constructs that map cleanly to RDF.

